RVEY OF NEW ENGLAND HOSPITAL LIBRARIES.THE NEW ENGLAND LIBRARY ASSOCIATION'S HOSPITAL LIBRARY SECTION SENT AQUESTIONNAIRE TO 472 LOCAL HOSPITALS, WITH 159 USABLE RESPONSES. ITS ORIGINALPURPOSE WAS TO PROVIDE HOSPITAL LIBRARIANS WITH A PROFILE OF COLLEAGUES AND TOASSIST IN GENERAL PLANNING. QUESTIONS CONCERNED SIZE AND TYPE OF HOSPITAL;NUMBER, SALARY, AND CHARACTERISTICS OF STAFF; AND LIBRARY BUDGET, COLLECTION,AND SERVICES. THE RESPONSES ARE TABULATED AND DISCUSSED